name: 01 - Lesson 1 - Main Text.mp3
format: mp3
duration: 02:09.541
id: c272e50e-46be-42cd-beb8-6db89296dd46
clips:
  - id: 09016a75-793a-433f-8136-197b9b4d2f72
    start: 00:15.18
    end: 00:19.18
    fields:
      transcription: 最近、ホテルで正月を過ごす人が増えたそうである。
      meaning: Lately, an increasing number of Japanese have been spending the New Years holidays in hotels.
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 60651b29-af30-41eb-b50d-2e8d085cf6b9
    start: 00:20.04
    end: 00:24.22
    fields:
      transcription: 年末に家をしめて、家族全員でホテルに移る。
      meaning: "At the end of the year, entire families will shut up their homes and move to a hotel. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 3aa7541a-f3b3-4827-bcb9-2e7e6cc7c31e
    start: 00:25.24
    end: 00:30.38
    fields:
      transcription: ホテルでは正月特別の飾りをつけ、正月の料理を出す。
      meaning: "The hotels display special New Year's decorations and serve New Year's cuisine. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 89442181-5ee1-4dcd-822d-ddcb236dce6f
    start: 00:30.9
    end: 00:36.18
    fields:
      transcription: |-
        主婦も家事をする必要がない。
        家族揃ってゆっくりすごす。
      meaning: "Housewives are relieved of housework, and the whole family is able to enjoy a relaxing New Year's together. "
      notes: káji-o suru
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: ae56eb7b-e84f-4d4a-99aa-ac015b6a4c83
    start: 00:36.908
    end: 00:38.86
    fields:
      transcription: その理由はいくつかある。
      meaning: "There are several reasons for this phenomenon. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 5587c571-b30f-4285-8764-7f3d11d35351
    start: 00:39.5
    end: 00:43.98
    fields:
      transcription: 主人も主婦も忙しくて、正月の準備ができない場合もある。
      meaning: "Sometimes, both husband and wife are too busy to prepare for the New Years holidays. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 27f0840e-5eb9-4876-878b-801e0c04cc19
    start: 00:44.76
    end: 00:48.06
    fields:
      transcription: 正月の伝統的な行事が嫌いな人もある。
      meaning: "Some families dislike the traditional New Year's rituals. "
      notes: shougatsu-no dentouteki-na gyóuji-ga kirai-na hitó-mo áru
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 7a80031d-8c81-458c-a218-cc93f0ec3b0b
    start: 00:48.68
    end: 00:53.8
    fields:
      transcription: "正月に大ぜいの客が来るので、会うのがめんどうだと思う人もある。 "
      meaning: "Others do not want to have to take care of the large number of visitors who show up during the holidays. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: aef7846d-958b-4929-a404-9d214f1857c5
    start: 00:55.12
    end: 01:06.1
    fields:
      transcription: むかしは、正月にはいつもより綺麗な物を着て、いつもよりぜいたくな料理を食べ、遠くから親せきの人が集まって、にぎやかに話し合った。
      meaning: "In the past, Japanese dressed in especially elegant clothes on New Year's, and dined on an unusually lavish spread. They enjoyed lively conversation with relatives from distant places. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 4b689ce2-16a6-4eae-bbbf-81706e288997
    start: 01:06.9
    end: 01:12.76
    fields:
      transcription: 子供達も、正月には特別にお金をもらって、好きな物を買うことができた。
      meaning: "Children received a special gift of money to buy something they liked. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 045b6428-5dc4-4ea3-bde6-ae37f0822db7
    start: 01:13.4
    end: 01:17.56
    fields:
      transcription: 正月は、「いつもと違う」ぜいたくをするときであった。
      meaning: "New Year's was a time for unusual luxury and elegance. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 2a818cf0-8c4d-4b3d-b2f6-ec86e9130bb6
    start: 01:18.46
    end: 01:25.18
    fields:
      transcription: そのためには家中をよく掃除し、正月のための特別の飾りをつけた。
      meaning: "For that reason, families cleaned their whole houses thoroughly and put up special New Year's decorations. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: c2374f00-ea3a-4f69-9175-ed8dbf6a2147
    start: 01:25.94
    end: 01:30.6
    fields:
      transcription: 家を大切にしたのは、家が生活の場所だったからである。
      meaning: "The home was central to Japanese lifestyles, and was kept in top condition for that reason. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 40fe680e-f519-4ca3-884c-84eeafcc2981
    start: 01:31.5
    end: 01:34.74
    fields:
      transcription: 今は住宅の利用法が変わった。
      meaning: "Japanese no longer use their homes in this fashion. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: ab6137a6-f3d2-45b3-a4ae-3e7c6d23084c
    start: 01:35.5
    end: 01:43.42
    fields:
      transcription: 自分の家で結婚式や祝いの宴会をする人は少ない。たいていの人がホテルを使う。
      meaning: "Few modern Japanese hold weddings or celebratory parties in their homes—most prefer hotels. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: d8898763-97ae-4069-937d-0d39b003c04e
    start: 01:43.78
    end: 01:47.28
    fields:
      transcription: 人にごちそうするときにはレストランに行く。
      meaning: "Guests are entertained at restaurants. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 714e67bd-99de-496d-9f6f-7fae6937a648
    start: 01:47.68
    end: 01:51.08
    fields:
      transcription: 人と話をするときは喫茶店で会う。
      meaning: "People meet in coffee houses to talk. "
      notes: hito-to hanashí-o suru-tóki-wa
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 92e59754-9251-4f42-88c2-ba59706796f3
    start: 01:51.4
    end: 01:55.5
    fields:
      transcription: その上正月まで、ホテルで過ごす人が増えた。
      meaning: "And families stay in hotels through the New Year's holidays. "
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 2bfa92ec-5ae1-4dba-ae3d-2123d7190b18
    start: 01:56.44
    end: 02:00.88
    fields:
      transcription: 今の大都会の住宅は、何をするところであろう。
      meaning: One wonders about the function of the home in the cities of today.
    tags:
      - iij01
  - id: 24886d69-6e4b-4507-86eb-2d20cc25989b
    start: 02:01.02
    end: 02:09.12
    fields:
      transcription: テレビを見て、寝るところか。 住宅というより、個室か寝室になったのであろうか。
      meaning: Has it become merely a place for watch- ing TV and sleeping? If so, the Japanese home is no longer a home. It's a private chamber or bedroom instead.
    tags:
      - iij01
